  "prompt": "How much to charge for glowsticks at a party 50 person Halloween party? I don\u2019t want to seem miserly at a party where everything else is free",
  "response": "For a 50-person Halloween party, here are some pricing suggestions:\n\nFree options:\n- Give them away completely free as part of the party fun\n- Include them in the party cost/admission\n\nLow-cost options:\n- $0.50-$1 per glowstick\n- Bulk pack price (if you bought them in advance)\n- Offer at \"cost\" to just cover your expense\n\nConsiderations:\n- If everything else is free, giving them away free fits the party vibe\n- Bulk glowsticks can be very cheap (like 25-50 cents each)\n- Consider having some free, some for sale\n- Could do a \"donation\" jar instead of set price\n\nBest approach depends on:\n- Your budget\n- Party atmosphere\n- Guest expectations\n\nGenerally, for a Halloween party, free or very low cost works best to keep the fun mood.",
